'this' refers to the object that called the function. Its value depends on how the function is called.

```javascript
// Method: this = object
const obj = {
    name: 'Alice',
    greet() { console.log(this.name); } // 'Alice'
};

// Regular function: this = undefined (strict) or window
function show() { console.log(this); }

// Arrow function: this = enclosing lexical scope
class Timer {
    tick() {
        setInterval(() => {
            console.log(this); // Timer instance, not window
        }, 1000);
    }
}

// Explicit binding
func.call(obj, arg1);   // this = obj
func.apply(obj, [args]); // same, array args
const bound = func.bind(obj); // returns new function
```

